Currently it is supported by Spring Boot out of the box.

Besides the property, dependency `org.hibernate:hibernate-micrometer` has to be on classpath. Compare [Spring Actuator documentation][1].

Previously you could create a `HibernateQueryMetrics` bean as described in [this micrometer issue][2].

```java
@Bean
MeterBinder hibernateQueryMetrics(EntityManagerFactory entityManager) {
    return new HibernateQueryMetrics(entityManager.unwrap(SessionFactoryImplementor.class), &quot;hibernateSession&quot;, Tags.empty());
}
```

Support for hibernate metrics has been moved from micrometer to hibernate project.

  [1]: https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current/reference/htmlsingle/#actuator.metrics.supported.hibernate
  [2]: https://github.com/micrometer-metrics/micrometer/issues/1006#issuecomment-1058014616

